In [ ]:
b,a=plt.subplots(3,2)
x= np.arange(1,5)
a[0][0].plot(x,x*x)
a[0][0].set_title('square')
a[0][1].plot(x,np.sqrt(x))
a[0][1].set_title('square root')
a[1][0].plot(x,np.exp(x))
a[1][0].set_title('exp')
a[1][1].plot(x,np.log10(x))
a[1][1].set_title('log')
a[2][1].plot(x,np.log10(x))
a[2][1].set_title('log')
a[2][0].plot(x,np.log10(x))
a[2][0].set_title('log')
plt.suptitle('math functions')
plt.show()

python_course_green='skyblue'
fig =plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))

sub1=plt.subplot(2,2,1)
sub1.set_xticks(())
sub1.set_yticks(())
sub1.text(0.5,0.5,'Fig(2,2,1)',ha='center',va='center',size=20,alpha=.5)

sub2=plt.subplot(2,2,2)
sub2.set_xticks(())
sub2.set_yticks(())
sub2.text(0.5,0.5,'subplot(2,2,2)',ha='center',va='center',size=20,alpha=.5)

sub3=plt.subplot(2,2,3)
sub3.set_xticks(())
sub3.set_yticks(())
sub3.text(0.5,0.5,'subplot(2,2,3)',ha='center',va='center',size=20,alpha=.5)

sub3=plt.subplot(2,2,4,facecolor=python_course_green)
sub3.set_xticks(())
sub3.set_yticks(())
sub3.text(0.5,0.5,'subplot(2,2,4)',ha='center',va='center',size=20,alpha=.5,color='purple')

fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()
